Patient: What kind of exercise is best for my heart condition?

Healthcare Educator: Walking, cycling, or simple bodyweight exercises can help.

Patient: I can't afford a gym membership. What can I do?

Healthcare Educator: You can walk or cycle in the park. For strength, do bodyweight exercises at home.

Patient: I'm always so busy. How can I fit exercise into my schedule?

Healthcare Educator: Try to set aside a specific time each day, even if it's just 15-20 minutes. 

Patient: How will these exercises help my heart?

Healthcare Educator: Regular exercise strengthens your heart, reduces symptoms, and improves your overall health. 

Patient: But I always feel tired. Is it safe for me to exercise?

Healthcare Educator: Start slow and gradually increase. Listen to your body and rest when needed.